SIMPLE: extravaganza
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extravaganza
<hw>Ex*trav`a*gan"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Extravagance</ets> with an Italian ending: cf. It.
<ets>stravaganza</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A composition, as in
music, or in the drama, designed to produce effect by its wild
irregularity; esp., a musical caricature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An extravagant flight of sentiment or
language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a lavish or spectacular show or event, or
presentation; <as>as, Disney staged an <ex>extravaganza</ex> in Central
Park that drew many thousands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extravagate</ent>⟦br⟧
